s they grow, obliging the weaver to return to repair them. Focusing on Renaissance England's perplexing sense of its time-boundedness, Escobedo presents early national consciousness as stranded awkwardly between the premodern and modern.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish literaturexHistory and criticismyEarly modern, 1500-1700. 0aLiterature and historyxHistoryxEngland. 0aNationalism and literaturexHistoryy16th centuryxEngland. 0aNationalism and literaturexHistoryy17th centuryxEngland. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aMedieval & Renaissance Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172396440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501723964423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501723964/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles